      "content": "Hello student! Today we learn about semiconductor devices. Diode is like a one-way street for electricity. BJT uses small base current to control large collector current. MOSFET uses voltage to control current.",
      "derivations": [
        {
          "title": "Diode Equation",
          "steps": [
            "I_D = I_S(e^(V_D/nV_T)-1)",
            "V_T = kT/q = 26mV at 300K",
            "I_S = reverse saturation current (very small)",
            "For V_D >> V_T: I_D ≈ I_S e^(V_D/nV_T)",
            "For V_D << -V_T: I_D ≈ -I_S (reverse bias)"
